Privacy Policy for Terreno App
Effective Date: [2024/10/7]
At [Terreno] (referred to as "we", "our", or "Terreno"), your privacy is important to us. This privacy policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our mobile application, which allows users to book stadiums and manage their bookings.
1. Information We Collect
We collect personal information necessary to provide our services. This includes, but is not limited to:

Personal Identifiable Information: Name, phone number, and other details provided during the registration process.
Booking Information: Details related to your stadium bookings, such as the stadium name, time, and category of the booking.
Device Information: Information such as your device type, operating system, and app usage data may be collected to improve our services.
Location Data: With your permission, we may collect location data to personalize your experience, such as showing nearby stadiums.
2. How We Use Your Information
We use the collected information to provide and improve our services:

Managing Bookings: Personal data is used to allow users to book stadiums and manage their reservations.
Customer Support: To assist with any issues or queries you may have regarding your bookings or account.
Transaction Processing: To process any payments or refunds related to bookings.
Personalization: To customize your experience, such as showing relevant stadium options based on your preferences or location.
Communication: To send notifications, reminders, or updates regarding bookings, promotions, or policy changes.
3. Sharing Your Information
We take your privacy seriously and do not sell or rent your personal information to third parties. However, we may share your information in the following circumstances:

With Consent: If you provide explicit consent, we may share your data with third parties for specific purposes.
Legal Obligations: We may disclose your information if required by law or legal processes, such as court orders or government investigations.
Service Providers: We may share your information with trusted third-party service providers who assist us in operating the app, such as payment processors or customer support providers, under strict confidentiality agreements.
4. Accessing and Deleting Your Information
You have the right to access, update, or delete your personal information. To do this:

Access: You can request access to your data by contacting us via the app or through our support channels.
Deletion: You can request the deletion of your account and associated data by contacting our support team. Once deleted, your account cannot be recovered, and your booking history will no longer be accessible.
5. Data Security
We take appropriate measures to protect your data, including:

Encryption: We use encryption technologies to protect sensitive information during transmission.
Secure Storage: Your data is stored on secure servers protected by firewalls and access controls.
Authentication: We use secure authentication methods to ensure only authorized users can access their accounts.
Despite our best efforts, no system can guarantee 100% security, and we encourage users to take precautions such as using strong passwords and securing their devices.

6. Data Retention
We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to provide the services outlined in this privacy policy or as required by law. If you delete your account, we will retain booking history for legal, regulatory, or accounting purposes for the necessary retention periods.

7. Cookies and Tracking Technologies
We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to:

Enhance User Experience: Keep you logged in, save preferences, and personalize content.
Analytics: Collect usage data to improve our appâ€™s performance and functionality.
You can manage cookie settings through your browser, though disabling cookies may impact your app experience.

8. Opting Out of Data Collection
You can opt out of certain data collection practices, such as marketing communications or location tracking:

Non-Essential Data: You may opt out of receiving promotional messages or limit data collection through your account settings or by contacting us.
Location Data: You can disable location services through your device settings.
Please note that some essential data, such as your name and phone number, is required to use key features like bookings.

9. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this privacy policy periodically. If any material changes are made, we will notify you via email or an in-app notification. It is your responsibility to review these changes.

10. Your Rights
You have the right to:

Access: Request access to the personal information we hold about you.
Correction: Request corrections to any inaccurate or outdated information.
Deletion: Request deletion of your account and personal data.
Objection: Object to the processing of your data for certain purposes, such as direct marketing.
To exercise these rights, please contact us at the provided support channels.

11. Account Deletion
You can request to delete your account at any time by contacting our support team. Please note that account deletion is permanent, and you will not be able to recover your booking history or account data once deleted.

12. Contact Information
If you have any questions or concerns about this privacy policy or your data, please contact us at:

Email: [nihady.hasan@gmail.com]
Phone: [+964-751-152-87-45]
13. Children's Privacy
Our services are not directed to individuals under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children under 13. If we learn that we have collected information from a child under 13, we will delete it immediately. If you believe we have collected such information, please contact us.

14. International Data Transfers
Your data may be transferred to, and processed in, countries outside of your own, where data protection laws may be different. We take appropriate safeguards to ensure that your data is protected, such as through standard contractual clauses or other legal mechanisms.

This privacy policy was last updated on [2024/10/7]. Please check back regularly for updates.
